Kinda boring website with the raw orbital data of everything this side of the moon: https://www.space-track.org/auth/login
Interesting visualizer using the data from the boring website above: https://whatsin.space
5-minutely updates from US Geostationary weather satellites: https://weather.cod.edu/satrad/?parms=continental-conus-02-24-0-100-1&checked=map&colorbar=undefined
Daily updates of nightime light emissions using polar LEO sats: https://www.ncei.noaa.gov/maps/VIIRS_DNB_nighttime_imagery/
Ground track visualizer of cool satellites you can listen to with a HAM radio: https://www.n2yo.com
